<p>Recently spotted <a href="https://github.com/stardiviner/mu4e-marker-icons">mu4e-marker-icons</a>, which adds mu4e icons using <a href="https://github.com/domtronn/all-the-icons.el">all-the-icons</a>.</p>
<p>Although I'm not currently using all-the-icons, it did remind me to take a look at mu4e's built-in variables to spiff up my email. It's pretty simple. Find the icons you like and set them as follows:</p>
<p><img src="https://xenodium.github.io/images/mu4e-icons/mu4eicons.png" alt=""></p>
<pre><code class="language-{.commonlisp">(setq mu4e-headers-unread-mark    '(&quot;u&quot; . &quot;ğŸ“© &quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-draft-mark     '(&quot;D&quot; . &quot;ğŸš§ &quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-flagged-mark   '(&quot;F&quot; . &quot;ğŸš© &quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-new-mark       '(&quot;N&quot; . &quot;âœ¨ &quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-passed-mark    '(&quot;P&quot; . &quot;â†ª &quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-replied-mark   '(&quot;R&quot; . &quot;â†© &quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-seen-mark      '(&quot;S&quot; . &quot; &quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-trashed-mark   '(&quot;T&quot; . &quot;ğŸ—‘ï¸&quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-attach-mark    '(&quot;a&quot; . &quot;ğŸ“ &quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-encrypted-mark '(&quot;x&quot; . &quot;ğŸ”‘ &quot;))
(setq mu4e-headers-signed-mark    '(&quot;s&quot; . &quot;ğŸ–Š &quot;))
</code></pre>
